{
  "name": "Audit: Asana Writes",
  "version": "1.1.0",
  "description": "Logs every Asana write operation to audit trail after execution.",
  "when": {
    "type": "postToolUse",
    "toolTypes": [
      "@mcp.*asana.*"
    ]
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "STEP 1 \u2014 GATE CHECK: READ ops (GetTask, SearchTasks, GetTasksForProject) \u2192 STOP immediately. Only WRITE ops proceed: UpdateTask, CreateTask, CreateTaskStory, SetParentForTask, AddTagForTask, RemoveTagForTask.\n\nSTEP 2 \u2014 EXTRACT from tool response: task_gid (never guess), task_name, fields_modified (list), result.\n\nSTEP 3 \u2014 CRITICAL RULES:\n- One UpdateTask with multiple fields = ONE log entry.\n- One log entry per task_gid \u2014 never combine multiple tasks.\n- Batch of N tasks = N separate entries.\n- Result field: success|failure|blocked only (never 'write').\n- JSONL: APPEND only \u2014 never overwrite or truncate.\n\nSTEP 4 \u2014 LOG:\n1. JSONL (primary): APPEND to ~/shared/context/active/asana-audit-log.jsonl: {\"timestamp\":\"ISO-8601\",\"tool\":\"tool_name\",\"task_gid\":\"gid\",\"task_name\":\"name\",\"project\":\"PROJECT_ID\",\"fields_modified\":[\"f1\",\"f2\"],\"result\":\"success|failure|blocked\",\"notes\":\"context\"}.\n2. DuckDB (fallback, continue if fails): INSERT INTO asana.audit_log same fields.\n\nPROJECT_ID: AU|MX|WW_Testing|WW_Acquisition|Paid_App|My_Tasks|ABPS_AI_Content. Pipeline writes: add \"pipeline_agent\"+\"pipeline_stage\".\n\nWORKED EXAMPLE: UpdateTask(gid=1234, due_date='2026-04-25', assignee='1212732742544167') \u2192 {\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-22T04:40:00Z\",\"tool\":\"UpdateTask\",\"task_gid\":\"1234\",\"task_name\":\"Review doc\",\"project\":\"My_Tasks\",\"fields_modified\":[\"due_date\",\"assignee\"],\"result\":\"success\",\"notes\":\"rescheduled+reassigned\"}."
  }
}